{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"STATE: OPEN, NOT built — ESCALATED. HMAC scheme removal (contract phase) + expand-contract migration doc (docs/migrations/hmac-opcert-removal.md). BLOCKED on a design fork coupled to ee0b: removing HMAC requires the gate PRODUCERS to mint asymmetric op-certs, which needs the producer-key decision — (A) every environment (incl local dev) holds its own Ed25519 op-cert key and signs locally, vs (B) only the trusted rebar-mcp server (ee0b) signs and local runs produce unsigned records. This intersects ee0b's double-signing question (review_plan self-signs HMAC today). Must be designed with ee0b. Description carries the expand/contract artifact spec."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784001354598184001,"uuid":"e9bb8c28-bbb8-47b1-9726-96af4c2d427c"}